In [[management]], a '''line function''' is any kind of daily operation such as [[purchasing]], [[manufacturing]], and [[marketing|selling]] that is directly involved in carrying out the purpose of an [[organization]]. This contrasts to a [[staff function]] (such as the [[human resources]] department), which involves the provision of advice and other support to those involved in a line function.

